caption: Best sushi in old town :)

I'm from Asia country, so I really know the sushi's taste. I've been several sushi restaurants in Chicago, but they didn't satisfy me well. Café sushi located in heart of Old town in Chicago which is really great location. Especially, this sushi restaurant have a great rice taste and the sushi rolls were SO delicious!  and  Also, the service was great too. I can't wait to go back!!!
By far my favorite Sushi restaurant in all of Chicago! Amazing food, amazing drinks, and amazing prices!
The food is very delicious and service is good enough. B.Y.O.B is great!
I love this place
Go ! Go! Go!
Love Cafe Sushi! It is a little gem in Old Town. Sushi has always been delicious and the BYOB policy makes it even better. Service can be slow sometimes so factor that into your dining plans.

Terrible place . Overpriced Jewel quality of sushi . I will make extra effort to go somewhere else. Just ordered to go 2 rolls that on the web site were priced as $11 and $12 my bill was over $31. When I asked why server told me that they just had recent price increase...lough out loud Sishi was bad and small. Just recently went to new place in Lincoln Park called Kizumi sushi and for 2 delicious rolls I paid $26 . The place on Wells i will definitely not recommend to anyone. Decor is old and staff not attentive.

We stopped by on Friday night. social distancing on Wells was horrible but Cafe Sushi seemed ok. We ordered our food... waited, waited... appetizer came. Waited 40 more minutes for 2 rolls. Not busy outside.. other tables served on and off. Finally the waiter came outside.. clearly confused where the plate was going. He set it down at another table where the couple NOT wearing masks (as none of us do once  seated), told him it was not theirs. He then proceeded to pick it up but kept it in front of them while they argued back and forth. He finally realizes it’s ours, on the entire other side of patio.. places it in front of us. We said no thanks. He gave it to another couple, virus going on and none of us wearing masks once at tables. Sent it back and we left without paying. Sorry. It’s a virus and I don’t trust anyone I don’t know.. barely trust the people I do know. Won’t go back.
Be prepared to wait 30 minutes for your pickup order
Very upset! The website said it was open, just tried calling multiple times and it was closed. I’ve never tried the sushi here before, so just  ended up going for sushi down the street!
Delicious sushi, the Philly Roll is my favorite! Great BYOB restaurant to enjoy a good meal at!
pretty ok sushi BYOB so don't forget to stop on your way
The decor is a little dingy; the food was delicious; the service is friendly but not so efficient :)

Been going here for 15 years. Staff is always very friendly. Great bang for the buck BYOB spot in Old Town. Spicy Tuna has always been my fav. Never had another spicy tuna quite like it. Good stop before going out after to The Second City, River North, lakefront, or just another bar in Old Town. Love the BYOB aspect. Not too many in Old Town I don't think. Patio is great when it's warm.
Love coming to this local sushi spot. BYOB is an added benefit. Always good service and good fish. Great for a casual date night!
Delicious sushi at a reasonable price. It’s also BYOB which is great. Highly recommend!
The food is really well prepared, looks and taste awesome!
Bad sushi. Bad service.

This restaurant exists only because of its location and no competition in the vicinity. I live close by and had many attempts of visiting it. The food is ok, some items are even good. But it will take 40 min or more before they bring anything and sometimes they bring not what you ordered. Attention is poor, the check that you receive might be somebody else's.  The carpet inside stinks. I prefer to sit outside,  but if you have a party of more than 4, they would refuse to put the tables together. Manager never comes out to speak with you and if you are unhappy with something you are just supposed to suck it up.

READ THIS This place is truly horrible, we came here in a group and we wanted to sit outside. We were a group of 6 people and wanted to sit together, and not separately. We were told that there was a "policy" and, that we could not move the tables together. So we called the manager to clarify that the policy was in use, the waitress just left for a while (and did not get the manager.), and told us that the "manager told her" that we could not move the tables together due to the "policy". Keep in mind that the manager was at the restaurant, at least according to the waitress. The waiters people  skills where horrible because she kept saying the same thing over and over again. The food also takes literally 1 hour to come Eventually we ended up leaving, and the restaurant lost business because of the "policy". It also screwed up our whole evening and it also forced us to go to the different restaurant.

READ THIS REVIEW BEFORE COMING!!!!! 1. THE CARPET SMELLS AND THERE IS NO AC 2. The food takes 100 years to come. 3. We called the manager and he didn't come 4. This is horrible for groups, we came in a group and wanted to sit outside, but we couldn't move the tables together. And when we wanted the manager to come, the waiter told us that the manager couldn't come and there was a "policy" that was nonexistent 5.service is the CRAPPIEST I'VE EVER SEEN. Waiter's people skills are horrible!!!!!  Just please, do me a favor and DO NOT COME HERE!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!!
Awesome flower bomb maki!
I love those korean servers so fast and kind.
Nice staff, quick service. Salmon was bland at best, didn’t have much flavor at all.

I never write reviews - but the service here is terrible.  It’s mediocre sushi at a fair price with BYOB which is nice.  But I waited 3 hours for half my order (this was me giving the place a 2nd chance).  Just go to a real restaurant if you’re an adult and put any value whatsoever on your time.
Affordable option if you’re looking for a sushi dinner however the rolls were average and the service was kind of slow.
Veggie friendly sushi place. I never have to think whether the place has something for me. I have been coming here for 20 years and I think this place is a Haven for someone like me.
Verrryyy slow service ~ average/good sushi. + byob, patio seating, decent prices.
Went on a Friday at 8:30. Food wasn't served for over an hour. It was pretty good but nothing special. BYOB is very nice. But if you're looking for specifically sushi I'd go elsewhere.
very good food moderately priced byob you need to bring your own wine or beer

I haven't been here in over ten years because I never really thought the sushi here was impressive; but today was warm and I wanted to relax outside and order a few maki rolls. I chose a cucumber maki, asparagus, spicy tuna and spicy salmon.  I found the fish to be strange tasting so to disguise the odd taste I ordered extra wasabi to drown out the fish which I could tell was most definitely not fresh.  The cucumber and asparagus maki rolls were good but I noticed there was too much rice in each maki roll. I was impressed with the service here because everyone is friendly but I just didn't find the maki rolls were  as fresh tasting as they should have been and I'm a huge fan of sushi. Prices are reasonable and the maki never fell apart but the taste is mediocre and I'm very fussy when it comes to ordering sushi or sashimi so I was disappointed with my dining experience here.  If you aren't super fussy like me you might enjoy your meal here but I'm very particular about my sashimi and sushi and I prefer a higher grade fish.  Prices here are extremely reasonable but as I stated earlier the flavors and textures here are lacking.
They never disappoint! Mango habanero and orange rolls are a must.
Excellent

Good local place.

An excellent place without inflated prices. BYOB make is even more reasonable. Great service, fresh food, very pretty decor, attention to detail.  Highly recommended!

Just another ok sushi restaurant. The sushi I had wasn't very fresh.
Sushi is good enough. Service was a little slow, but overall a pleasant experience.  They do have gluten free soy sauce available.
This is good for sit down or take out. Sushi is not the best but it's very good and it's reliable. The service is good and everybody is friendly is also very easy to get into

Sushi was fine, but the service the night we went was super slow. It took almost an hour to get our food. We were the only table in the restaurant for about 20 minutes and there was one couple that walked in for a takeout order.

I don’t really love sushi but I really like this place. Also BYOB which I always love
solid sushi.....and byob! We will be back....
No frills sushi spot, quite and BYOB. Inexpensive, fresh fish and fast service. Can be in and out for a snack on less than 30 minutes
This place is new from the look and feel of it but the food was on point. Excellent sushi & potstickers!

His restaurant is trash and either racist or have the worst service ever!!My cousin and I walked in on Saturday May 26 around 4 pm. We sat outside and placed order with the waiter (Asian guy with a earring in his left ear.) We preceded to chat for what had to be 45 mins to an hour without water or utensils being brought out. Keep in mind, only 3 tables in this entire restaurant are occupied including us.  By the time we looked up the table next to us called the waiter over and was asking for their water. He brought the water 30 secs later. At that point we looked around and saw everyone (7 tables or so) all with water and utensils. Our waiter came back like 1 min with the 2 rolls (no utensils or plates) right before we were going to walk out. He then told me We have nothing because of a shift change. After he left I went inside and told him and the other waiter to comp our meal for the atrocious service in which they declined. Never go it’s horrible. Needless to say we left the sushi and definitely won’t return. Don’t go no customer service. We only ordered two rolls and they wouldn’t como it. Not even give us a free dessert or something.
Great rolls and service. Four stars only because I tend to like a good crowd and this place is consistently pretty quiet. Recommend
Great sushi in a beautiful neighborhood.
The service can be slow and the sushi is just OK.
Remember BYOB. Can get busy
Superfun place for sushi in Old Town on wells street.  Great quality sushi, excellent service, and it's BYOB.  Grab a bottle and a few friends and head on over.  ( Try the Alaska Don!)

The sushi here was well price. We went here on a Friday night on a cold December evening. We got there around 9 p.m. and there was no wait. We were told on the phone though, that there is often a 20 to 30 minute wait at this time. After ordering food, it took 20 to 30 minutes to come. The restaurant was only about 75% capacity. I think the wait stemed from the quality of sushi they were making, because when it came out we were not disappointed. The tamago or egg Sushi was also pleasantly surprisingly good. For an appetizer we had well done, but not over fried, gyoza. The seaweed salad was regular and I probably wouldn't order it again in the future.  It's BYOB so make sure to bring through that alcohol!
Favorite sushi place in Chicago!

I see nothing wrong with some awesome ass sushi. L was in town and she loves this place, made it the perfect reason to go there.  BYOB with no corkage fee. AWESOME  Some of my faves for the evening- the Hawaiian maki, the honeybee maki, the mexican maki (spicy), the firecracker maki  We got 7 rolls and the 4 of us were stuffed. And the best part? The bill was 25$ each. Can you say happy tummy sushi time?  The place itself seems like it could be a date place but isn't really because of it being neat and utilitarian as well. There is outdoor as well as bar seating for you finicky types  The waiter service is definitely slow but I think that was due to a lack of waiters. However you can order with any of them at any time and they are happy to help you. Just flag one down and be aggressive about it.  I will be back cafe sushi. You have intrigued me.
Very tolerant and kind staff! Good rolls and quick arrival!
Great quality fish, expensive but in a great neighborhood. Top-notch way to finish a night of parting in Old Town!

A disappointment. Ordered Tako Su and Sashimi Moriwase. Tako Su - barely any sauce at the bottom of the dish, could not dip the octopus pieces properly and they weren't good on their own. Sashimi Moriwase - tuna did not feel fresh, salmon wasn't melting in the mouth. Whatever the other two kinds of fish there were - one was ok, the other firm and tasteless. So much for "chef's choice".

Your standard sushi joint to get a few rolls. It's byob and in a pretty convenient location, so I often order take-out here.

Best sushi and very nice atmosphere.  I often come to Chicago from Appleton Wisconsin and this is definitely one of our favorite stops.  To be honest, once my daughter and I drove there (3 hours) JUST to eat at this café.  That's how awesome it is.
The same servers for 4 years - awesome! BYOB and sit outside for some people watching in the summer. Nothing out of the ordinary, just very fresh sashimi.

We've been coming here for 4 years and the sushi is consistently good. It's a great BYOB, but also good for grabbing and taking back home if you live in Old Town. Their Honey Bee roll is our favorite, but we've also enjoyed the Snow White, Mexican, Firecracker and Sahara. Weekend evenings get very busy in the summer (there's a small outside patio) so expect a wait.
For the price, you get very high quality sushi. The staff is friendly and very personable. They have outdoor seating that allow you to really embrace the Old Town vibe. A must-try in the city!

Have been coming here for years. We love this place! My whole family enjoys the food here. The prices are great and the food is delicious. Never have been disappointed here, and I have probably had just about everything on the menu.  Its BYOB so come prepared.

Sushi was expected for price. High energy setting with friendly staff and modern decor. Sushi and food preparation area open and visible to customers and well maintained. Chefs and staff are clean, polite and prompt. I would definitely return.
Honey bee role was one of the best ive ever had. Viagra was very good as well.
